sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K389411
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part combines a mutated ''virG'' response regulator from the VirA/G receptor system under the control of a constitutive promoter with a sensitivity tuner before a luciferase gene under the control of a ''vir'' promoter. The sensitivity tuner enhances a signal from a promoter so it enhances the readout luciferase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: * luciferase from pGL4.10luc2 (Promega) * sensitivity tuner part, terminators and constitutive promoter from the partsregistry * ''virG'' was synthesized by Mr. Gene * ''vir'' promoter from ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' C58, TI-plasmid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: sensitivity tuner to enhance the luciferase signal

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K389401
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a modified <partinfo>I746370</partinfo> sensitivity tuner. Instead of a GFP reporter, this one has a firefly luciferase (from Promega's pGL4.10luc2 vector) as one reporter gene. The arabinose promoter has been removed from the original part so now it is possible to assemble this part behind any promoter to get an enhanced luciferase signal.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: * luciferase from pGL4.10luc2 (Promega) * the rest from the partsregistry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: arabinose promoter removed, GFP exchanged with luciferase compared to the original part <partinfo>I746370</partinfo>

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: virG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the ''virG'' response regulator from the virA/G receptor system. The virA/G receptor system is used by ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' to detect phenolic substances secreted by plants. In presence of these substances, ''virG'' is activated by the ''virA'' receptor and induces the transcription of genes under the control of a ''vir'' promotor. Normally, ''virG'' needs the ''rpoA'' RNA polymerase subunit from ''A. tumefaciens'' to work in ''Escherichia coli'' but this ''virG'' BioBrick is mutated, so works with the ''rpoA'' subunit from ''E. coli''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: synthesized by Mr. Gene, so optimated codon usage, removal of illegal restriction sites

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746360
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PF promoter taken from the P2 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PF promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The original source is the P2 phage genome. For our work the DNA came from plasmids, kindly supplied to us by Prof. Calendar, University of California (Berkeley): Bacteriophage PSP3 and fR73 Activator Proteins: Analysis of Promoter Specificities; Julien and Calendar, 1996; JOURNAL OF BACTERIOLOGY, Oct. 1996, p. 5668???5675
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no special considerations seemed necessary
